02:59.379 --> 03:02.181
I wish you wouldn't
do that around me.
It's so filthy!

03:02.182 --> 03:05.818
Don't give me a problem
about the cigarettes.
It's such a filthy habit.

03:05.819 --> 03:07.309
Oh, my God!

03:07.454 --> 03:08.944
Look at this.

03:10.791 --> 03:14.488
Oh, Jesus.
This is so appalling.

03:15.696 --> 03:17.696
I can't believe it.

03:17.698 --> 03:20.166
I can't believe
they gave it to him.

03:26.440 --> 03:28.441
Ah, this is pathetic.

03:28.442 --> 03:30.743
Now he's a loser
with a Jaguar.

03:30.744 --> 03:33.679
Seriously,
who did he have to blow
to get that thing?

03:35.649 --> 03:37.850
Good morning, sir.
Mr. Willis.

03:37.851 --> 03:39.285
It's really a...

03:39.286 --> 03:40.617
Mr. Trask!

03:41.188 --> 03:42.688
Quite a piece
of machinery.

03:42.689 --> 03:45.291
Good morning, Havemeyer.
Morning to you, sir.

03:45.292 --> 03:46.452
Bene!

03:46.660 --> 03:48.594
Bene?
Bene! Fabulous!

03:48.595 --> 03:49.962
What's fabulous?

03:49.963 --> 03:52.264
That fine piece of steel
you have back there.

03:52.265 --> 03:54.325
Ah, you don't think
I deserve it.

03:54.835 --> 03:56.669
No, sir.
On the contrary.

03:56.670 --> 03:58.704
I think
it's great.

03:58.705 --> 04:01.407
Why should the
headmaster of Baird
be seen putt-putting

04:01.408 --> 04:03.242
around in some junker?

04:03.243 --> 04:05.811
In fact, I think the
board of trustees have had

04:05.812 --> 04:09.181
their first true stroke
of inspiration in some time.

04:09.182 --> 04:11.684
Well, thank you,
Havemeyer.

04:11.685 --> 04:13.853
I'll take that at face value.

04:13.854 --> 04:15.947
I'd expect
nothing less, sir.

04:16.723 --> 04:18.350
Have a good day.

04:20.726 --> 04:22.661
Morning,
Mrs. Hunsaker.
Good morning.

04:22.662 --> 04:25.325
What have we here,
Murderer's Row?

04:32.038 --> 04:33.305
What was that about?

04:33.306 --> 04:34.840
Nothing. Just saying hello.

04:34.841 --> 04:37.037
I like to say hello
to Headmaster Trask.

04:38.044 --> 04:41.180
Sugarbush. Lift tickets
and condo vouchers.

04:41.181 --> 04:43.048
I thought we were
going to Stowe.

04:43.049 --> 04:45.084
Sugarbush
is Stowe, Jimmy.

04:45.085 --> 04:46.852
This year we're
doing it right.

04:46.853 --> 04:49.688
Thanksgiving in Vermont,
Christmas in Switzerland...

04:49.689 --> 04:51.924
Christmas in Gstaad
is gonna cost us...
"Staad."

04:51.925 --> 04:53.292
The "G" is silent.

04:53.293 --> 04:54.818
"Staad." George?

04:55.095 --> 04:56.495
"Staad."
Trent?

04:56.496 --> 04:58.798
"Staad," man.
So what about Staad?

04:58.799 --> 05:00.666
Fine. The "G" may
be silent,

05:00.667 --> 05:03.402
but it's gonna take at least
three grand to get there.

05:03.403 --> 05:05.104
I'll have to talk
to my father.

05:05.105 --> 05:07.873
Better yet,
have my father
talk to your father.

05:07.874 --> 05:09.843
Or my father
talk to your father.

05:12.312 --> 05:14.280
You going home
this weekend, Chas?

05:15.081 --> 05:17.283
I don't know.

05:17.284 --> 05:20.019
You going home
to fuckin' Idaho
for Thanksgiving?

05:20.020 --> 05:21.544
I'm from Oregon.

05:22.088 --> 05:24.356
I meant
fuckin' Oregon.

05:24.357 --> 05:26.392
Charlie, how do you
feel about skiing?

05:27.694 --> 05:30.459
You in the mood for
the white-bosomed
slopes of Vermont?

05:32.332 --> 05:33.832
Got a deal going.

05:33.833 --> 05:35.301
20% off for
my friends.

05:35.302 --> 05:36.835
My father set it up.

05:36.836 --> 05:38.337
Christmas
in Switzerland.

05:38.338 --> 05:40.673
Staad.
Gstaad.
Dropping the "G" is phony.

05:40.674 --> 05:42.308
You said
everybody
says "Staad."

05:42.309 --> 05:43.808
Not if you've
been there.

05:43.843 --> 05:47.213
Easter in Bermuda,
then Kentucky Derby
weekend.

05:47.214 --> 05:49.415
We could fit
you in, kid.

05:49.416 --> 05:53.352
Well, how much are
these white-bosomed
slopes of Vermont?

05:53.353 --> 05:55.354
1,200.

05:55.355 --> 05:59.625
Includes a nine-course,
champagne
Thanksgiving dinner.

05:59.626 --> 06:03.362
$1,200 is a little rich
for my blood, Harry.

06:03.363 --> 06:05.497
Well, how short
are you?

06:05.498 --> 06:07.666
How short, Harry?

06:07.667 --> 06:11.297
So short it wouldn't be
worth the trouble
of you and George to measure.

06:11.438 --> 06:12.972
But thanks for askin',
all right?

06:12.973 --> 06:14.440
Mmm-hmm.

06:14.441 --> 06:16.175
If you change
your mind...

06:16.176 --> 06:18.611
What'd you do that for?
You know he's on aid.

06:18.612 --> 06:20.112
On major
holidays, Willis,

06:20.113 --> 06:21.880
it's customary
for the lord of the manor

06:21.881 --> 06:23.182
to offer drippings
to the poor.

06:23.183 --> 06:24.582
You're so
full of shit!

06:51.678 --> 06:52.907
Hi. Mrs. Rossi?

06:53.213 --> 06:54.407
Yes?

06:54.681 --> 06:56.376
I'm here about
the weekend job.

06:58.285 --> 07:00.219
Come on in.

07:04.424 --> 07:07.960
Does he got pimples?
He hates pimples.

07:07.961 --> 07:09.561
Francine, be quiet.

07:09.562 --> 07:12.157
Pimples.
Pimples. Yeah.

07:12.365 --> 07:13.732
Shush!

07:13.733 --> 07:16.702
I'm sorry. The school
gave me your name,
but I've forgotten it.

07:16.703 --> 07:18.270
It's Charlie Simms.

07:18.271 --> 07:20.306
How are you,
Charlie?
Fine, thanks.

07:20.307 --> 07:21.467
Right this way.

07:25.312 --> 07:27.680
You're available
the whole weekend?

07:27.681 --> 07:28.981
Yeah.

07:28.982 --> 07:30.916
Not going home
for Thanksgiving?
No.

07:30.917 --> 07:32.180
Good.

07:34.421 --> 07:37.389
They put him in
a veteran's home,
but he hated it,

07:37.390 --> 07:39.518
so I told my dad
that we'd take him.

07:41.861 --> 07:44.997
Before you go in,
do you mind my
telling you a few things?

07:44.998 --> 07:48.935
Don't "sir" him
and don't ask him
too many questions.

07:49.436 --> 07:51.670
And if he
staggers a little
when he gets up,

07:51.671 --> 07:53.139
don't pay
any attention.

07:54.474 --> 07:58.433
Charlie,
I can tell you're
the right person for the job.

07:58.978 --> 08:01.209
And Uncle Frank's
gonna like you a lot, too.

08:03.216 --> 08:05.851
Where you gonna be
this weekend?

08:05.852 --> 08:08.014
We're driving to Albany.

08:08.655 --> 08:12.182
Donny, my husband,
has family there.

08:17.564 --> 08:19.331
Do you want
Tommy in or out?

08:19.332 --> 08:20.899
Leave him out!

08:20.900 --> 08:24.530
He's chasing that
Calico ginch from
the track houses again!

08:30.710 --> 08:33.543
Down deep, the man
is a lump of sugar.

08:53.733 --> 08:55.267
Sir?

08:55.268 --> 08:57.236
Don't call me sir.

08:57.237 --> 08:58.804
I'm sorry.

08:58.805 --> 09:00.506
I mean mister, sir.

09:00.507 --> 09:04.676
Uh-oh, we got a moron here,
is that it?

09:04.677 --> 09:06.245
No, mister...

09:06.246 --> 09:07.736
That is...

09:08.882 --> 09:11.717
Lieutenant.
Yes, sir...

09:11.718 --> 09:13.618
Lieutenant Colonel.

09:13.987 --> 09:17.855
Twenty-six years on the line,
nobody ever busted me
four grades before.

09:18.825 --> 09:20.452
Get in here,
you idiot!

09:27.434 --> 09:30.631
Come a little closer.
I wanna get a
better look at you.

09:39.446 --> 09:41.846
How's your skin, son?

09:42.649 --> 09:44.216
My skin, sir?

09:44.217 --> 09:45.951
Oh, for
Christ's sake.

09:45.952 --> 09:48.921
I'm sorry, I don...
Just call me Frank.

09:48.922 --> 09:50.756
Call me Mr. Slade.

09:50.757 --> 09:54.591
Call me Colonel,
if you must. Just don't
call me sir.

09:55.895 --> 09:57.727
All right, Colonel.

09:59.599 --> 10:01.033
Simms, Charles.

10:01.034 --> 10:02.401
A senior.

10:02.402 --> 10:04.269
You on
student aid, Simms?

10:04.270 --> 10:05.931
Yes, I am.

10:06.372 --> 10:08.341
For "student aid"
read "crook."

10:09.776 --> 10:13.111
Your father
peddles car telephones
at a 300% markup.

10:13.112 --> 10:15.948
Your mother works
on heavy commission
in a camera store.

10:15.949 --> 10:18.917
Graduated to it
from espresso machines.

10:25.658 --> 10:29.151
What are you, dying of
some wasting disease?

10:31.297 --> 10:33.288
No, I'm right...
I'm right here.

10:34.000 --> 10:36.731
I know exactly where
your body is.

10:37.103 --> 10:40.073
What I'm lookin' for
is some
indication of a brain.

10:41.107 --> 10:43.599
Too much football
without a helmet?

10:44.143 --> 10:47.477
Hah! Lyndon's line
on Gerry Ford.

10:48.882 --> 10:52.651
Deputy Debriefer, Paris,
Peace Talks, '66.

10:52.652 --> 10:56.714
Snagged the Silver Star
and a silver bar.
Threw me into G-2.

10:57.524 --> 10:58.824
G-2?

10:58.825 --> 11:01.988
Intelligence,
of which you have none.

11:06.199 --> 11:07.598
Where you from?

11:08.268 --> 11:09.792
Gresham, Oregon,

11:11.838 --> 11:13.071
Colonel.

11:13.072 --> 11:15.632
What does your daddy do
in Gresham, Oregon?

11:16.142 --> 11:18.076
Hmm?
Count wood chips?

11:19.212 --> 11:23.081
My stepfather and my mom
run a convenience store.

11:23.082 --> 11:26.143
How convenient.
What time they open?

11:27.020 --> 11:28.187
5:00 a.m.

11:28.188 --> 11:29.246
Close?

11:29.489 --> 11:30.756
1:00 a.m.

11:30.757 --> 11:32.658
Hard workers.

11:32.659 --> 11:34.559
You got me all
misty-eyed!

11:38.865 --> 11:41.698
So, what are you doing here
in this sparrow-fart town?

11:42.802 --> 11:44.930
I attend Baird.

11:46.406 --> 11:47.896
Attend Baird!

11:49.309 --> 11:52.010
I know you go
to the Baird school.

11:52.011 --> 11:55.047
Point is,
how do you afford it,

11:55.048 --> 11:59.747
even with the student aid
and the folks back home
hustlin' corn nuts?

12:01.154 --> 12:04.990
I won a Young American
merit scholarship.

12:04.991 --> 12:06.823
Hoo-ah!

12:08.661 --> 12:12.120
Glory, glory
Hallelujah

12:12.665 --> 12:16.124
Glory, glory
Hallelujah

12:20.440 --> 12:21.532
Who's there?

12:22.208 --> 12:23.938
That little
piece of tail?

12:27.213 --> 12:29.081
Get her outta here!

12:37.657 --> 12:39.022
Yeah.

12:40.827 --> 12:42.818
Can't believe
they're my blood.

12:48.167 --> 12:52.204
IQ of sloths and
the manners of banshees.

12:52.205 --> 12:54.806
He's a mechanic,
she's a homemaker.

12:54.807 --> 12:57.276
He knows as much about cars
as a beauty queen,

12:57.277 --> 13:00.337
and she bakes cookies,
taste like wing nuts.

13:01.080 --> 13:03.845
As for the tots,
they're twits.

13:04.617 --> 13:07.484
How's your skin, son?
I like my aides
to be presentable.

13:10.790 --> 13:12.324
Well, I...

13:12.325 --> 13:14.020
I've had a few zits.

13:15.295 --> 13:17.663
But my roommate,
he lent me his Clinique

13:17.664 --> 13:20.032
because he's from
Chestnut Hill
and he's got...

13:20.033 --> 13:22.695
"The History of My Skin,"
by Charles Simms.

13:24.003 --> 13:26.597
You patronizing me,
peewee? Hmm?

13:27.373 --> 13:30.104
You givin' me
that old prep school
palaver?

13:31.444 --> 13:32.673
Baird School!

13:34.247 --> 13:37.649
A bunch of runny-nosed
snots in tweed jackets

13:37.650 --> 13:40.176
all studyin'
to be George Bush.

13:42.355 --> 13:44.356
Well...

13:44.357 --> 13:47.053
I believe President Bush
went to Andover, Colonel.

13:50.463 --> 13:52.795
You sharpshootin'
me, punk?

13:54.233 --> 13:56.259
Is that what
you're doin'?

13:57.236 --> 13:59.571
Don't you
sharpshoot me.

13:59.572 --> 14:02.107
You'll give me 40.

14:02.108 --> 14:04.743
Then you're gonna give me
40 more.

14:04.744 --> 14:08.480
Then you're gonna
pull K.P.,
the grease pit!

14:08.481 --> 14:12.317
I'll rub your nose
in enlisted men's crud

14:12.318 --> 14:14.252
till you don't
know which end is up!

14:14.854 --> 14:16.117
You understand?

14:17.457 --> 14:18.657
Yeah.

14:18.658 --> 14:19.989
What do you want?

14:20.159 --> 14:22.160
What do you mean,
what do I want?

14:22.161 --> 14:23.595
What do you want here?

14:26.199 --> 14:28.030
I want a job.

14:28.868 --> 14:30.769
A job!

14:30.770 --> 14:33.004
Yeah, I want a job
so I can make, you know,

14:33.005 --> 14:35.770
my plane fare home
for Christmas.

14:36.743 --> 14:39.803
Oh, God,
you're touching!

14:52.225 --> 14:55.327
They used to waltz on the banks

14:55.328 --> 14:58.764
Of the mighty Mississippi

14:58.765 --> 15:02.565
Loving the whole
night through

15:04.003 --> 15:07.639
Till the riverboat gambler

15:07.640 --> 15:10.709
Went off to make a killin'

15:10.710 --> 15:13.645
And bring it on back to you

15:14.747 --> 15:16.648
Still here, poormouth?

15:16.649 --> 15:17.946
Hmm?

15:19.419 --> 15:21.353
Convenience store,

15:21.354 --> 15:22.617
my ass!

15:23.856 --> 15:27.918
Hustlin' jalapeno dips
to the appleseeds.

15:29.028 --> 15:30.621
Go on.

15:31.431 --> 15:32.921
Dismissed.

15:36.035 --> 15:37.526
Dismissed!

15:45.244 --> 15:48.180
Evangeline

15:48.181 --> 15:50.945
Evangeline

15:51.684 --> 15:53.985
Mrs. Rossi?

15:53.986 --> 15:56.512
Charlie, we're up here!
Come on up.

15:58.925 --> 16:01.416
This is Donny.
Hey, Charlie.

16:01.861 --> 16:03.090
Hi.

16:03.496 --> 16:06.465
Mrs. Rossi, I got
the feelin' I screwed up.

16:06.666 --> 16:08.900
Oh, you couldn't have.

16:08.901 --> 16:10.502
It was a
bad interview.

16:10.503 --> 16:12.471
That was no interview,
Charlie. You're it.

16:12.772 --> 16:15.874
You're the only
one that showed up.
You have to take the job.

16:15.875 --> 16:20.506
He sleeps a lot. You can
watch television,
call your girlfriend.

16:21.180 --> 16:23.114
I promise you,
an easy 300 bucks.

16:24.183 --> 16:26.709
I don't get
an easy feeling.

16:30.356 --> 16:32.324
His bark is worse
than his bite.

16:33.459 --> 16:36.827
He was a great soldier,
a real hero.

16:38.631 --> 16:40.465
The man grows on you.

16:40.466 --> 16:42.560
By Sunday night,
you'll be best friends.

16:43.870 --> 16:46.566
Charlie, please.

16:47.273 --> 16:49.774
I want to get
away with my husband
for a few days,

16:49.775 --> 16:51.710
and Uncle Frank
won't come with us.

16:52.712 --> 16:55.580
Six months ago,
he could sometimes tell
light from dark,

16:55.581 --> 16:57.549
but now there's nothing.

16:57.550 --> 17:00.576
I just feel better
having someone else
around just in case.

17:07.226 --> 17:08.522
Please?

17:11.797 --> 17:12.992
Okay, Mrs. Rossi.

17:13.432 --> 17:14.559
Sure.

17:14.733 --> 17:17.002
Thank you, Charlie.

17:17.002 --> 17:18.435
Come here, you.

17:26.712 --> 17:28.546
There you go.

17:28.547 --> 17:30.914
Chas. Chas, hold up.

17:32.451 --> 17:34.686
How you doin'?
I'm good.

17:34.687 --> 17:35.984
That's great.

17:36.555 --> 17:38.615
This can't go out.
This is on reserve.

17:42.295 --> 17:43.956
Here's the thing.

17:44.297 --> 17:46.822
I need the book tonight

17:47.667 --> 17:50.535
for a Thanksgiving quiz
with big-shit Preston
in the morning.

17:50.536 --> 17:52.971
Yeah, I know.
That's why he
put it on reserve.

17:52.972 --> 17:54.339
This is our only copy.

17:54.340 --> 17:56.775
Chas, I'm pullin'
an all-nighter.

17:56.776 --> 17:59.438
Without that book
I'm dead, okay?

18:01.414 --> 18:04.916
If it's not back
by 7:30, it's gonna
be my ass.

18:04.917 --> 18:07.011
Oh, I promise.
I promise.

18:15.928 --> 18:17.919
Got it?
Yeah.

18:32.611 --> 18:34.876
Just a second.
I gotta lock up.

18:39.518 --> 18:40.884
Okay.

18:42.455 --> 18:45.117
God, can you wait
to get out of this
dump or what?

18:50.763 --> 18:53.631
Where you guys
going skiing again?
Sugarloaf or...

18:53.632 --> 18:55.567
It's bush, Chas,
Sugarbush.

19:05.745 --> 19:07.445
That's my boys.

19:07.446 --> 19:09.481
What are you doin'?

19:09.482 --> 19:12.450
Keep your voice down!

19:12.451 --> 19:14.786
I'll tell you about it
in the morning.

19:17.423 --> 19:18.788
What...

19:19.759 --> 19:21.359
Mrs. Hunsaker,
have a nice day?

19:21.360 --> 19:23.128
George, why
all the noise?

19:24.797 --> 19:27.632
It's Hunsaker! Go! Go!

19:27.633 --> 19:29.801
I was just
messin' around with Chas.

19:29.802 --> 19:31.069
Good evening, Charles.

19:31.070 --> 19:32.435
Hi, Mrs. Hunsaker.

19:38.210 --> 19:40.372
What was that?
I don't know, ma'am.

19:40.880 --> 19:42.147
Who were
those boys?

19:42.148 --> 19:43.945
Oh, who knows?
What were they doing?

19:44.183 --> 19:45.878
Charles?

19:46.285 --> 19:47.619
Um...

19:47.620 --> 19:49.687
Did you make this
scarf yourself?

19:49.688 --> 19:51.289
No, George,
I bought it.

19:51.290 --> 19:54.092
'Cause it's a beauty.
It really is.
Thank you, George.

19:54.093 --> 19:56.824
In case I don't
see you before
the Thanksgiving holidays,

19:57.263 --> 19:58.930
why don't you give me
one of your big hugs?

19:58.931 --> 20:00.432
Oh, George!
Please?

20:00.433 --> 20:01.933
Good evening, boys.
Come on.

20:01.934 --> 20:03.334
Goodbye,
Mrs. Hunsaker.

20:25.157 --> 20:28.059
Mr. Trask is our
fearless leader,

20:29.361 --> 20:32.422
a man of learning,
a voracious reader.

20:34.066 --> 20:36.865
He could recite the lliad
in ancient Greek

20:38.003 --> 20:41.371
while fishing for trout
in a rippling creek.

20:42.675 --> 20:46.702
Endowed with wisdom,
of judgment sound,

20:47.279 --> 20:51.216
nevertheless about him
the questions abound.

20:57.056 --> 21:00.617
How does Mr. Trask
make such wonderful deals?

21:01.193 --> 21:04.789
Why did the trustees
buy him Jaguar wheels?

21:05.798 --> 21:07.561
He wasn't conniving.

21:08.134 --> 21:10.235
He wasn't crass.

21:10.236 --> 21:12.602
He merely
puckered his lips

21:15.441 --> 21:17.809
and kissed their ass!

21:36.128 --> 21:37.562
Come on.

21:37.696 --> 21:39.130
Come on.

21:43.536 --> 21:44.736
One more.

21:44.737 --> 21:46.034
One more, come on!

22:05.825 --> 22:07.224
Fuck you!

22:14.066 --> 22:17.434
Mr. Simms, Mr. Willis.

22:18.103 --> 22:19.196
Hmm.

22:20.639 --> 22:22.941
Mrs. Hunsaker says
that you gentlemen

22:22.942 --> 22:24.909
were at a vantage
point last night

22:24.910 --> 22:28.346
to observe who was
responsible for this

22:29.381 --> 22:30.678
stunt.

22:36.622 --> 22:37.953
Who was it?

22:39.091 --> 22:41.116
I really couldn't
tell you, sir.

22:42.795 --> 22:45.897
I thought I saw
someone fooling
with the lamppost,

22:45.898 --> 22:50.335
but by the time
I pulled focus,
they were gone.

22:51.370 --> 22:52.701
Mr. Simms?

22:54.506 --> 22:55.997
I couldn't say.

22:58.244 --> 23:02.313
That automobile
is not just a
possession of mine.

23:02.314 --> 23:07.252
That automobile was
presented to me by
the board of trustees.

23:07.253 --> 23:10.321
It is a symbol of
the standard of
excellence

23:10.322 --> 23:12.557
for which this
school is known,

23:12.558 --> 23:15.288
and I will not
have it tarnished.

23:16.328 --> 23:17.728
The automobile?

23:19.698 --> 23:21.826
The standard,
Mr. Willis.

23:25.371 --> 23:27.396
What's your position,
Mr. Simms?

23:28.240 --> 23:29.641
On what, sir?

23:29.642 --> 23:31.906
On preserving the
reputation of Baird.

23:32.177 --> 23:33.907
I'm for Baird.

23:34.446 --> 23:35.914
Then, who did it?

23:37.249 --> 23:39.377
I really
couldn't say for sure.

23:45.057 --> 23:46.582
Very well.

23:54.099 --> 23:56.768
First thing Monday,
I'm convening
a special session

23:56.769 --> 23:59.103
of the student-faculty
disciplinary committee.

23:59.104 --> 24:01.873
As this is a matter
which concerns
the whole school,

24:01.874 --> 24:04.776
the entire student body
will be present.

24:04.777 --> 24:07.412
There will be
no classes,
no activities.

24:07.413 --> 24:09.981
Nothing will
transpire at
this institution

24:09.982 --> 24:12.917
until that proceeding
is concluded.

24:15.154 --> 24:18.419
And if, at that time,
we are no further
along than we are now,

24:20.526 --> 24:22.323
I will expel you both.

24:27.666 --> 24:30.294
Mr. Willis,
would you excuse us?

24:34.773 --> 24:36.366
Have a nice Thanksgiving.

24:38.143 --> 24:39.877
Thank you.
You, too, Mr. Willis.

24:39.878 --> 24:41.175
I will.

24:49.321 --> 24:50.584
Mr. Simms,

24:52.691 --> 24:54.887
I'm not quite through
with you yet.

25:03.702 --> 25:06.504
One of the few perks
of this office is that

25:06.505 --> 25:11.636
I am empowered to handle
certain matters on
my own as I see fit.

25:13.479 --> 25:15.213
Do you understand?

25:15.214 --> 25:16.772
Yes, sir.
Good.

25:17.249 --> 25:20.451
The Dean of
Admissions at Harvard
and I have an arrangement.

25:20.452 --> 25:23.821
Along with the usual
sheaf of applicants
submitted by Baird,

25:23.822 --> 25:25.890
of which virtually

25:25.891 --> 25:28.861
two-thirds are
guaranteed admittance,

25:29.661 --> 25:31.653
I add one name,

25:33.265 --> 25:36.860
somebody who's a standout
and yet underprivileged.

25:38.036 --> 25:40.338
A student who
cannot afford to pay

25:40.339 --> 25:42.205
the board and
tuition in Cambridge.

25:44.810 --> 25:48.371
Do you know on whose behalf
I drafted a memo this year?

25:49.581 --> 25:50.648
No, sir.

25:50.649 --> 25:51.878
You.

25:52.851 --> 25:54.410
You, Mr. Simms.

25:57.656 --> 25:59.886
Now can you tell me
who did it?

26:02.428 --> 26:03.918
No, sir, I can't.

26:05.297 --> 26:08.164
You take the weekend
to think about it, Mr. Simms.

26:10.636 --> 26:12.468
Good afternoon.

26:15.474 --> 26:16.964
What'd he say?

26:17.443 --> 26:19.644
Nothin'.
What do you
mean, nothing?

26:19.645 --> 26:21.179
He said the
same thing.

26:21.180 --> 26:22.447
He just said
it over.

26:22.448 --> 26:24.182
You know what
he's doing?

26:24.183 --> 26:26.913
He's good-cop,
bad-coppin' us.

26:27.486 --> 26:29.754
He knows I'm old guard.
You're fringe.

26:29.755 --> 26:32.349
He's gonna bear down on me
and soft-soap you.

26:33.459 --> 26:36.594
Did he try to
soft-soap you?

26:36.595 --> 26:37.756
Did he?

26:38.564 --> 26:39.656
No.

26:40.799 --> 26:44.035
Chas, I detect a slight
panic pulse from you.
Are you panicking?

26:44.036 --> 26:45.536
Yeah, a little.

26:45.537 --> 26:47.699
Come on.
You're on
scholarship, right?

26:48.907 --> 26:50.074
Yeah.

26:50.075 --> 26:53.170
You're on scholarship
from Oregon at Baird.

26:54.513 --> 26:56.709
You're a long way
from home, Chas.

26:57.382 --> 26:59.510
What's that got
to do with anything?

27:00.018 --> 27:02.420
I don't know how
it works out there.

27:02.421 --> 27:04.088
But how it
works here?

27:04.089 --> 27:05.819
We stick together.

27:05.991 --> 27:08.459
It's us against them,
no matter what.

27:08.460 --> 27:10.361
We don't cover our ass.

27:10.362 --> 27:12.463
We don't tell our parents.

27:12.464 --> 27:14.159
Stonewall everybody!

27:15.300 --> 27:17.168
And above all,

27:17.169 --> 27:19.971
never, ever

27:19.972 --> 27:23.101
leave any of us
twisting in the wind.

27:24.843 --> 27:26.611
And that's it.

27:26.612 --> 27:29.380
What does that have
to do with me being
on scholarship?

27:29.381 --> 27:31.315
Hey, hey.

27:31.316 --> 27:34.081
I'm just tryin' to
bring you up to speed,
kid, that's it.

27:35.287 --> 27:36.618
Thanks.

27:39.758 --> 27:43.353
I'll tell you what.
Give me a few hours
to figure out the moves,

27:44.029 --> 27:45.690
and call me tonight
in Vermont.

27:47.533 --> 27:50.768
I'll be at
the Sugarbush lodge,
all right?

27:50.769 --> 27:51.930
All right.

27:53.405 --> 27:54.873
You all right?

27:56.074 --> 27:57.633
Yeah, I guess so.

27:59.144 --> 28:00.441
Okay.

28:03.048 --> 28:05.383
Try to keep him down
to four drinks a day.

28:05.384 --> 28:08.319
If you can keep
him down to 40,
you're doin' good.

28:08.320 --> 28:10.955
We try to water
them down a little.
Do you know how to do that?

28:10.956 --> 28:12.924
It's a long ride,
honey.

28:13.525 --> 28:15.560
Get the bags in the car.
I'll be right out.

28:15.561 --> 28:19.190
Mommy, Mommy,
don't forget
Uncle Frank's walk.

28:20.866 --> 28:22.959
Oh, yeah.

28:23.769 --> 28:28.035
You have to air him
out a little every day.

28:29.942 --> 28:32.610
Why don't you
go on back there,
get yourself oriented?

28:32.611 --> 28:35.672
I'll come out in a minute,
give you telephone
numbers and stuff.

28:37.616 --> 28:39.951
Well, I wouldn't
try a thing like that

28:39.952 --> 28:42.119
unless I knew, would I?

28:42.120 --> 28:43.816
Just let me
speak to her.

28:44.189 --> 28:46.257
Hello, beautiful.
Is that you?

28:46.258 --> 28:48.317
Yeah,
we spoke yesterday.

28:51.029 --> 28:52.763
You have a glass
of wine with lunch?

28:52.764 --> 28:54.699
You sound
a little dusky. Hmm.

28:57.336 --> 28:59.236
Just a minute,
sweetheart.

29:00.872 --> 29:02.363
You're back, huh?

29:03.609 --> 29:05.009
Tenacious!

29:05.010 --> 29:08.079
Get out my dress blues.
They're in a garment bag
in the closet.

29:08.080 --> 29:09.714
Check the
top dresser drawer.

29:09.715 --> 29:11.315
Take out
the shoulder boards

29:11.316 --> 29:13.184
and affix them,
shoulders
right and left,

29:13.185 --> 29:15.654
ASAP. That means now.

29:16.855 --> 29:18.456
Hello.

29:18.457 --> 29:21.392
Sorry to keep you
waiting, sweetheart.

29:21.393 --> 29:24.095
I'm not the kind of guy
who likes to rush things,

29:24.096 --> 29:27.064
but I'm catchin'
a 4:00 at Logan,
I'm lookin' out my window,

29:27.065 --> 29:28.829
and there's
not a taxi in sight.

29:30.068 --> 29:31.535
What happened
to Chet?

29:31.536 --> 29:33.334
He didn't invest
in a radio yet?

29:33.905 --> 29:36.875
Hah! Well,
get your driver on it.

29:38.343 --> 29:40.711
Tell him to get
a move on.

29:40.712 --> 29:43.238
Yes. Mmm.

29:44.416 --> 29:47.918
Some kind of body
has got to go with
that bedroom voice.

29:47.919 --> 29:50.411
One day I'm gonna swing by,
get a better look at it.

29:51.089 --> 29:52.216
You bet.

29:54.159 --> 29:55.422
Bye.

29:58.163 --> 30:00.298
My Valpak's
underneath the bed.

30:00.299 --> 30:01.799
Get it out.

30:01.800 --> 30:04.360
Put the boards
on the blues
and fold 'em in.

30:05.537 --> 30:08.105
Are we going
someplace, Colonel?

30:08.106 --> 30:09.767
What business is
that of yours?

30:10.542 --> 30:12.710
Don't shrug, imbecile.
I'm blind.

30:12.711 --> 30:15.112
Save your body language
for the bimbi.

30:15.981 --> 30:17.449
Now, get my gear out.

30:18.717 --> 30:21.083
Francine, get in the car.

30:21.520 --> 30:25.286
It's almost 3:00.
The goddamn Flintstones
haven't left yet.

30:25.891 --> 30:28.951
Willie Rossi
must go in the car.

30:30.629 --> 30:32.263
Here comes
Mrs. Rossi now.

30:32.264 --> 30:33.493
Damn it!

30:34.266 --> 30:36.428
She said goodbye to me
three times today.

30:37.803 --> 30:40.137
What has she got,
separation anxiety?

30:40.138 --> 30:41.970
Cut her off
at the door.

30:44.743 --> 30:46.472
Hi, honey.
Bye, honey.

30:51.049 --> 30:52.676
I wish you were
coming with us.

30:53.285 --> 30:54.618
Me, too.

30:54.619 --> 30:55.985
Maybe next time.

31:00.859 --> 31:02.193
Drive carefully now.

31:02.194 --> 31:03.388
Yeah.

31:04.830 --> 31:07.264
Charlie, this is
where we'll be.

31:08.700 --> 31:11.636
Good luck, Charlie.
Don't let him
drink too much.

31:15.841 --> 31:17.365
See you, Charlie.

31:18.243 --> 31:20.974
And no 000 numbers.
He loves to talk dirty.

31:29.454 --> 31:31.514
All right,
let's get to work.

31:40.799 --> 31:42.699
L- buckles
givin' you trouble?

31:44.736 --> 31:47.004
Never in the
Boy Scouts, sluggo?

31:47.005 --> 31:48.773
I made Tenderfoot.

31:48.774 --> 31:50.708
Tenderfoot,
my foot!

31:50.709 --> 31:53.007
Convenience store
mama's boy.

31:53.145 --> 31:55.045
Here. Let me
take a look
at that.

31:55.981 --> 31:59.383
Touch me again,
I'll kill you,
you little son of a bitch!

32:00.652 --> 32:02.143
I touch you.

32:04.256 --> 32:05.553
Understand?

32:07.959 --> 32:12.021
My shoulder boards are
in the top dresser drawer.
Get them, son.

32:12.597 --> 32:14.588
The epaulets with
the silver oak leaf.

32:33.084 --> 32:34.785
Are these the...

32:34.786 --> 32:36.584
Good.
Taxi come yet?

32:38.023 --> 32:40.491
Colonel,
where are we going?

32:40.492 --> 32:42.526
Where are we going?

32:42.527 --> 32:44.795
Freak show central.

32:44.796 --> 32:46.765
Where's that?
New York City.

32:49.601 --> 32:51.168
That's in New York, son.

32:51.169 --> 32:53.160
New York State.

32:53.371 --> 32:56.207
Mrs. Rossi didn't say
anything to me
about going anywhere.

32:56.208 --> 32:57.436
She forgot.

32:58.643 --> 33:00.344
Should we call her,
'cause I...

33:00.345 --> 33:02.012
You kidding me?

33:02.013 --> 33:04.148
Call her? By the time
they get to Albany

33:04.149 --> 33:05.816
in that Hupmobile
he drives

33:05.817 --> 33:08.047
it'll be opening day
at Saratoga.

33:08.520 --> 33:10.454
Colonel, I can't go
to New York City.

33:10.455 --> 33:11.582
Why not?

33:12.891 --> 33:14.290
New York...

33:14.759 --> 33:16.694
New York's too
much responsibility.

33:16.695 --> 33:18.596
Ah, responsibility!

33:18.597 --> 33:21.398
I had a lot
of 17-year-olds
in my first platoon.

33:21.399 --> 33:23.629
I took care of them.
All set!

33:26.071 --> 33:27.334
How do I look?

33:29.274 --> 33:30.969
Tickets. Money.

33:31.610 --> 33:32.838
Speech.

33:33.678 --> 33:37.012
Old Washington joke
from my days with Lyndon.

33:39.317 --> 33:41.385
I knew I could
count on transportation.

33:41.386 --> 33:42.717
Are you ready?

33:45.257 --> 33:47.817
This is not Panmunjom.
A simple yes will do.

33:48.927 --> 33:50.622
Um...
Good! Here you go.

33:50.996 --> 33:52.554
Come on!
Hop to, son!

33:53.965 --> 33:55.695
You're in front of me.
Let's go.

33:57.602 --> 33:59.400
Tomster,
come here, boy.

34:01.339 --> 34:02.606
Come on.

34:02.607 --> 34:04.642
Here, Tomster, come on.

34:04.643 --> 34:06.941
Tomster, Tomster. Yeah.

34:08.179 --> 34:11.274
Remember, when in doubt,

34:11.983 --> 34:13.110
fuck.

34:16.454 --> 34:18.889
Good afternoon, sir.
Where's our destination?

34:18.889 --> 34:22.126
Our destination
New York City,
home of the brave!

34:22.127 --> 34:24.194
We got two for
the shuttle
to New York.

34:24.195 --> 34:27.231
I'm not shuttling anywhere.
Look at those tickets.
First class.

34:27.232 --> 34:29.033
Yes, sir,
first class.

34:29.034 --> 34:31.101
Colonel,
you bought me
a ticket?

34:31.101 --> 34:32.870
I never said I'd
go to New York.

34:32.871 --> 34:34.905
What are you,
some kind of
chicken-shit,

34:34.906 --> 34:36.907
sticks to job
description only?

34:36.908 --> 34:38.842
Gate 46, sir.

34:38.842 --> 34:40.444
As you were, son.

34:40.445 --> 34:42.045
Thank you, sir.

34:42.047 --> 34:43.480
Which way's the door?

34:44.649 --> 34:47.751
Are you blind?
Are you blind?

34:47.752 --> 34:49.085
Of course not.

34:49.087 --> 34:51.556
Then why do you keep grabbin'
my goddamn arm?

34:51.989 --> 34:54.219
I take your arm.

34:58.763 --> 35:00.831
I'm sorry.
Don't be sorry.

35:00.832 --> 35:03.467
How would you know,
watchin' MTV all your life?

35:03.468 --> 35:05.562
Gentlemen?
Yeah!

35:08.173 --> 35:10.266
Jack Daniels.
You bet.

35:12.243 --> 35:14.144
And Diet Slice.

35:14.145 --> 35:15.479
The old Diet Slice.

35:15.480 --> 35:16.947
And a water.

35:16.948 --> 35:19.144
Thank you,
Daphne.
Certainly, sir.

35:26.591 --> 35:28.651
Mmm!
How did you
know her name?

35:30.962 --> 35:33.625
Well, she's
wearin' Floris.

35:34.566 --> 35:36.432
That's an
English cologne.

35:37.635 --> 35:40.935
But her voice is
California chickie.

35:41.740 --> 35:44.868
Now, California chickie
bucking for English lady.

35:45.677 --> 35:47.110
I call her Daphne.

35:49.347 --> 35:53.011
Oh, big things may
happen to that
little thing of yours.

35:55.253 --> 35:56.516
Look, Colonel,

35:58.356 --> 36:00.657
I'll get you to New York,
all right?
Uh-huh.

36:00.658 --> 36:03.423
Then I'm gonna have
to turn around and come back.

36:03.995 --> 36:06.293
Well, Chuck,
you gotta do
what you gotta do.

36:07.298 --> 36:08.789
Charlie, all right?

36:09.334 --> 36:10.667
Or Charles.

36:10.668 --> 36:13.037
Sorry.
I can't blame you, though.

36:13.038 --> 36:14.300
Chuck is a...

36:18.109 --> 36:20.411
So, why are we
going to New York?

36:20.412 --> 36:23.973
All information will be given
on a need-to-know basis.

36:25.417 --> 36:26.509
Hoo-ah!

36:27.318 --> 36:29.514
Where's Daphne?
Let's get her down here.

36:32.490 --> 36:34.049
She's in the back.

36:34.759 --> 36:36.193
A tail's in the tail.

36:37.595 --> 36:38.756
Hah!

36:39.531 --> 36:41.131
Oh, but I still smell her.

36:45.070 --> 36:46.230
Women.

36:47.639 --> 36:49.300
What can you say?

36:50.775 --> 36:52.266
Who made 'em?

36:53.478 --> 36:55.970
God must have been
a fuckin' genius.

37:00.351 --> 37:01.717
The hair...

37:03.054 --> 37:05.250
They say the hair
is everything, you know.

37:07.325 --> 37:11.057
Have you ever
buried your nose
in a mountain of curis

37:11.496 --> 37:14.625
and just wanted
to go to sleep forever?

37:16.367 --> 37:17.835
Or lips,

37:20.071 --> 37:22.206
and when they touched,
yours were like

37:22.207 --> 37:25.370
that first swallow of wine

37:25.910 --> 37:27.901
after you just crossed
the desert.

37:32.050 --> 37:33.484
Tits!

37:33.485 --> 37:34.679
Hoo-ah.

37:35.687 --> 37:38.179
Big ones, little ones,

37:39.124 --> 37:41.525
nipples staring
right out at you

37:41.526 --> 37:43.654
like secret searchlights.

37:44.696 --> 37:45.925
Mmm.

37:48.500 --> 37:49.728
And legs...

37:51.236 --> 37:54.228
I don't care if
they're Greek columns

37:54.606 --> 37:56.472
or secondhand Steinways.

37:58.009 --> 37:59.409
What's between 'em,

38:01.613 --> 38:03.171
passport to heaven.

38:05.083 --> 38:06.642
I need a drink.

38:10.622 --> 38:11.987
Yes, Mr. Simms,

38:13.992 --> 38:18.292
there's only two syllables
in this whole wide
world worth hearing.

38:23.868 --> 38:25.097
Pussy.

38:26.171 --> 38:27.468
Hah!

38:28.006 --> 38:30.908
Are you listening to me, son?
I'm givin' you pearis here.

38:32.844 --> 38:34.711
I guess you
really like women.

38:34.712 --> 38:37.238
Oh, above all things!

38:43.154 --> 38:46.556
A very, very
distant second

38:48.593 --> 38:49.890
is a Ferrari.

38:57.769 --> 38:58.895
Charlie?

39:01.873 --> 39:03.170
Give me your hand.

39:05.410 --> 39:08.277
This is just the start
of your education, son.

39:24.195 --> 39:25.390
Hoo-ah.

39:25.964 --> 39:27.431
Where are we?

39:27.432 --> 39:28.899
Where are we, eh?

39:29.467 --> 39:32.528
The cynosure of
all things civilized.

39:32.737 --> 39:34.637
The Waldorf-Astoria.

39:35.874 --> 39:39.443
The last time I
was here, Charlie,
was with a G-2 from Brussels.

39:39.444 --> 39:40.944
Had a Ferrari.

39:40.945 --> 39:44.314
Every day I
held the door open
for the fucker.

39:44.315 --> 39:46.583
Never even
offered me a ride.

39:46.584 --> 39:48.585
Well, fuck him.

39:48.586 --> 39:50.680
He's dead and I'm blind.

39:54.525 --> 39:56.093
Spread the word.

39:56.094 --> 39:57.327
Thank you, sir.

39:57.328 --> 39:59.363
And the intelligence
will be forthcoming?

39:59.364 --> 40:00.597
Sir?

40:00.598 --> 40:01.998
On the
escort scene.

40:02.667 --> 40:04.533
Yes, sir.

40:05.036 --> 40:07.070
And welcome to
the Waldorf.

40:07.071 --> 40:08.403
Gracias, amigo.

40:10.241 --> 40:11.775
Puerto Ricans.

40:11.776 --> 40:13.608
Always made
the best infantrymen.

40:21.119 --> 40:22.245
Oh!

40:29.360 --> 40:30.521
I'm home again.

40:31.562 --> 40:33.724
Give me an inventory
on this, will you?

40:39.904 --> 40:42.039
All right, where am I,
in Asia?

40:42.040 --> 40:45.242
He told me the phone
was on the other side
of the room, didn't he?

40:45.243 --> 40:46.608
By the windows?

40:48.146 --> 40:49.443
It's right here.

40:51.215 --> 40:52.547
Okay.

40:53.351 --> 40:54.614
We're in business.

40:59.590 --> 41:00.922
Get me the Oak Room.

41:02.527 --> 41:04.689
How's that inventory
comin'?

41:05.830 --> 41:08.665
There's Jim Beam

41:08.666 --> 41:11.234
and Early Times.

41:11.235 --> 41:13.067
Quartermaster's
on the take again.

41:13.504 --> 41:16.235
Hello. Is Sheldon
or Mack there?

41:17.975 --> 41:20.477
This is Lieutenant
Colonel Frank Slade.

41:20.478 --> 41:23.846
I used to be a regular.
I used to come in
with a General Garbisch.

41:26.017 --> 41:29.219
Yes, that's
probably because he's at
Arlington, six feet under.

41:29.220 --> 41:32.713
Listen up.
I want a table for two,
and I don't mean Siberia,

41:33.191 --> 41:34.283
15.

41:35.593 --> 41:37.494
Clear them little
bottles off.

41:37.495 --> 41:41.331
And when I get
off the phone,
call up Hyman.

41:41.332 --> 41:44.268
Tell him I want it
wall to wall
with John Daniels.

41:44.802 --> 41:47.738
Don't you mean
Jack Daniels?

41:47.739 --> 41:51.608
He may be Jack to you, son.
But when you've known him
as long as I have...

41:51.609 --> 41:53.076
That's a joke. Hello!

41:53.077 --> 41:56.179
This is Lieutenant
Colonel Frank Slade.
I would like a limo,

41:56.180 --> 41:57.512
00.

42:04.522 --> 42:06.490
What are you drinkin'?

42:06.491 --> 42:09.726
Nothing, thanks.
I don't use it.

42:09.727 --> 42:11.559
What's useful about it?

42:13.131 --> 42:16.430
I don't know.
Listen, Colonel,
I have to get going.

42:17.335 --> 42:18.935
Where you goin'?

42:18.936 --> 42:20.871
Back to school.
I've got some real

42:20.872 --> 42:22.999
important stuff I
have to take care of.

42:23.908 --> 42:25.399
Very well.

42:26.411 --> 42:29.679
But I never let
my aides leave
on an empty stomach.

42:29.680 --> 42:33.216
You'll dine with me
and then my driver
will transport you

42:33.217 --> 42:36.278
to the airport for
the Boston shuttle
departing at 2200 hours.

42:37.855 --> 42:41.257
Meanwhile,
unpack my bag.

42:41.759 --> 42:43.386
I'm gonna christen
the latrine.

42:45.963 --> 42:47.898
What's your name,
driver?

42:47.899 --> 42:49.099
Manny, sir.

42:49.100 --> 42:51.968
Manny. The bellhops
at the Waldorf,

42:51.969 --> 42:54.137
are they any good
at getting escorts?

42:54.138 --> 42:56.206
I wouldn't know, sir.

42:56.207 --> 42:57.741
What would you know?

42:57.742 --> 42:59.643
About what?

42:59.644 --> 43:01.339
About you-know-what?

43:02.880 --> 43:05.582
Maybe I could
manage something.

43:05.583 --> 43:08.018
I'm talkin'
top of the line, now.

43:08.019 --> 43:09.748
Let me think
about this, sir.

43:18.463 --> 43:20.997
What's the matter
with you?

43:20.998 --> 43:22.299
With me?

43:22.300 --> 43:25.001
Yeah. Car feels heavy.
You know why?

43:25.002 --> 43:27.870
You got the fuckin'
weight of the world
on your shoulders.

43:32.376 --> 43:34.678
I got a little problem
at school, that's all.

43:34.679 --> 43:36.046
Spit it out!

43:36.047 --> 43:37.714
It's not a big deal,
all right?

43:37.715 --> 43:39.783
Where we going,
the Oak Room
or somethin'?

43:39.784 --> 43:42.586
If it's not a big deal,
why did you say
real important stuff?

43:42.587 --> 43:44.754
What are you doin',
banging the dean's daughter?

43:44.755 --> 43:45.882
Hah!

43:48.092 --> 43:49.960
I'm just in
a little trouble.

43:49.961 --> 43:51.394
What kind of trouble?

43:52.129 --> 43:54.064
I saw some guys
doing something.

43:56.934 --> 44:00.336
To tell or not to tell,
or it's your ass.

44:00.938 --> 44:02.201
Hmm?

44:04.142 --> 44:05.408
How'd you know that?

44:05.409 --> 44:08.038
I'm a wizard.
Give me the details,
come on.

44:14.318 --> 44:16.319
There's this guy
at school named Harry.

44:16.320 --> 44:17.787
He's this
real rich kid,

44:17.788 --> 44:20.155
and he like,
runs the show.

44:20.958 --> 44:22.255
Who else?

44:23.761 --> 44:28.064
There's another guy, George,
but George didn't do anything.

44:28.065 --> 44:32.035
George and I saw
Harry and his buddies
doin' somethin'.

44:32.036 --> 44:34.170
Now, the folks at Baird,

44:34.171 --> 44:37.300
they know you and George
can identify
the guilty parties?

44:40.778 --> 44:42.379
Yeah, they think we can.

44:42.380 --> 44:44.348
George is
a friend of yours.

44:45.483 --> 44:47.317
He's not a friend,
but he's all right.

44:47.318 --> 44:48.717
You trust him?

44:49.587 --> 44:50.816
Yeah, I guess so.

44:51.022 --> 44:53.422
He's on
scholarship, too?

44:54.559 --> 44:55.856
No, why?

44:56.193 --> 44:59.329
We got George,
we got Harry,
we got trouble.

44:59.330 --> 45:02.232
They're rich, you're poor.
You wanna get rich.

45:02.233 --> 45:05.702
You wanna graduate Baird,
become a rich
big shot like them.

45:05.703 --> 45:07.203
Am I right?
No.

45:07.204 --> 45:09.002
It's not that
way at all.

45:09.607 --> 45:11.132
Okay, Charlie!

45:13.010 --> 45:15.502
Here we are, gentlemen,
the Oak Room.

45:16.013 --> 45:17.572
The Oak Room!

45:18.115 --> 45:21.184
Bring us a menu and
double Jack Daniels
on the rocks.

45:21.185 --> 45:23.186
Charlie, sit down here.

45:23.187 --> 45:25.952
Perhaps you'll feel more
comfortable in this, sir.

45:30.995 --> 45:34.329
You look great!

45:38.970 --> 45:40.597
Thank you.

45:41.739 --> 45:44.902
Here we are, Charlie,
the Oak Room.

45:45.676 --> 45:48.145
Now, read me
the bill of fare.

45:48.913 --> 45:50.437
Let's see.

45:50.881 --> 45:53.950
You got the Oak Room
burger and fries for $24.

45:53.951 --> 45:55.652
Where's the booze?

45:55.653 --> 45:57.287
Flowin' like
mud around here.

45:57.288 --> 45:58.756
A $24 hamburger?

46:00.291 --> 46:01.554
What's the story?

46:01.726 --> 46:03.193
What story?

46:04.595 --> 46:06.495
Are you a rich
miser or something?

46:06.931 --> 46:08.264
Hah!

46:08.265 --> 46:10.800
No, I'm just
your average blind man.

46:10.801 --> 46:12.531
Your average
blind man.

46:13.537 --> 46:16.268
How do you plan on paying
for all this stuff?

46:16.874 --> 46:18.774
Crisp, clean dollars.

46:19.143 --> 46:20.377
American.

46:20.378 --> 46:22.346
I saved up my
disability checks.

46:22.580 --> 46:25.749
How much did you save?
I mean, we flew first class,

46:25.750 --> 46:29.152
we're at the Waldorf-Astoria,
a $24 hamburger restaurant.

46:29.153 --> 46:31.087
All part of
a plan, Charlie.

46:31.522 --> 46:32.856
You want to let
me in on it?

46:32.857 --> 46:35.692
Why should I?
You're not interested.
You don't give a shit!

46:35.693 --> 46:40.130
You're leavin' on that
last shuttle
out of LaGuardia.

46:40.131 --> 46:41.894
Hmm? Ooh!

46:43.701 --> 46:46.534
You got 15 minutes, son.
I don't think
you're gonna make it.

46:47.304 --> 46:49.372
Unless the Oak Room
keeps some

46:49.373 --> 46:52.108
complimentary
helicopter on the roof.

46:52.109 --> 46:53.873
No, sir. No!

46:54.912 --> 46:56.846
You're here till tomorrow.

46:58.249 --> 47:00.650
You said the last shuttle
leaves at 2200 hours.

47:00.651 --> 47:02.585
That's 10:00, right?

47:03.387 --> 47:05.117
Last I heard, yeah.

47:05.823 --> 47:07.416
It's only 路:30.

47:07.858 --> 47:09.952
I lied. Leaves at 0:00.

47:10.661 --> 47:12.061
It leaves at 0:00?

47:12.229 --> 47:13.891
Calm down. Calm down.

47:15.833 --> 47:19.235
Ahh! The truth is,
Charlie,

47:21.205 --> 47:24.800
I need a guide dog
to help me execute my plan.

47:25.042 --> 47:26.567
What plan?

47:27.978 --> 47:29.674
You have a right to know.

47:31.348 --> 47:34.113
It's not really a plan,
Charlie. It's sort of a...

47:34.685 --> 47:36.654
More like a tour,

47:37.254 --> 47:39.689
a little tour
of pleasures.

47:40.358 --> 47:44.089
Stay in a first-class hotel,
eat an agreeable meal,

47:44.895 --> 47:47.125
drink a nice
glass of wine,

47:48.733 --> 47:50.433
see my big brother.

47:50.434 --> 47:53.203
Nothing like family,
you know.

47:53.204 --> 47:57.163
And then, make love
to a terrific woman.

47:59.477 --> 48:00.910
After that...

48:06.851 --> 48:08.114
Yeah?

48:10.554 --> 48:15.014
I'm gonna lie down on
my big, beautiful bed
at the Waldorf

48:15.259 --> 48:16.920
and blow my brains out.

48:20.831 --> 48:22.665
May I tell you
our specials?

48:22.666 --> 48:24.157
You may, sir.

48:24.735 --> 48:26.703
Tonight we have
charred venison with

48:26.704 --> 48:29.139
buckwheat spaetzle
and green peppercorn.

48:29.140 --> 48:32.876
Grilled veal paillards,
tomato tapenade,
and roasted eggplants.

48:32.877 --> 48:34.811
Get me a napkin.
My mouth's watering.

48:34.812 --> 48:37.113
If you would like our
cr路me souffl路 for dessert,

48:37.114 --> 48:39.115
it would be a good
idea to order now.

48:39.116 --> 48:43.076
Yes, on the souffl路.
Give us a half a minute
on the rest.

48:43.454 --> 48:44.922
Very good, sir.

48:49.193 --> 48:51.127
I'm leaning
towards the spaetzle.

48:51.128 --> 48:54.531
Colonel Slade...
Charlie, rolls on the table?

48:54.532 --> 48:55.799
Give 'em to me.

48:55.800 --> 48:58.101
You should
try these rolls, Charlie.

48:58.102 --> 49:01.704
I used to dream about them
when I was at Fort Huachuca.

49:01.705 --> 49:04.474
Colonel Slade...
Bread's no good
west of the Colorado.

49:04.475 --> 49:06.342
Water's too alkaline.

49:06.343 --> 49:09.108
Colonel Slade,
did you say...

49:09.513 --> 49:11.311
Did I hear you right?

49:12.650 --> 49:14.482
You said you're gonna
kill yourself?

49:15.085 --> 49:16.453
No.

49:16.454 --> 49:18.422
I said I was gonna
blow my brains out.

49:19.890 --> 49:21.791
Try one of these
rolls, Charlie.

49:21.792 --> 49:23.761
I buttered it for you.

49:24.428 --> 49:25.995
I don't want a roll,
all right?

49:25.996 --> 49:27.760
Okay. Have a radish!

49:28.666 --> 49:29.963
Hah!

49:31.368 --> 49:35.538
Hello! Bring me
a double Jack Daniels
on the rocks.

49:35.539 --> 49:36.836
Yes, sir.
Right away.

49:40.978 --> 49:43.345
Please, don't do that.

49:44.548 --> 49:46.107
Don't do that.

49:52.756 --> 49:53.883
Hmm.

49:57.228 --> 49:59.025
What a marvelous place.

50:02.800 --> 50:04.131
Okay.

50:08.138 --> 50:10.073
Yeah.

50:11.375 --> 50:13.434
Your billet is here.

50:14.011 --> 50:17.003
You'll find bedding
in the closet on the shelf.

50:18.048 --> 50:20.250
In the morning,
the area will be

50:20.251 --> 50:22.151
returned to
sitting-room mode

50:22.152 --> 50:24.451
no later than
0700 hours.

50:28.559 --> 50:29.924
What was that?

50:32.596 --> 50:33.825
Nothing.

50:34.899 --> 50:37.891
Next time
snap it out!

50:40.170 --> 50:44.437
Thumb to palm, index finger
through little digit,
smartly aligned,

50:45.776 --> 50:48.370
sharp to the hairline,
down!

50:52.983 --> 50:55.418
Too many men,
far better than you,

50:55.419 --> 50:57.387
have executed
that courtesy.

50:58.055 --> 51:01.150
And if you're smart,
you won't try it again.

51:05.296 --> 51:09.665
This bat has
got sharper radar
than the Nautilus.

51:10.167 --> 51:12.636
Don't fuck with me,
Charlie.

51:23.747 --> 51:26.239
See you get
a good night's
sleep, son.

51:38.429 --> 51:41.130
It's a lovely day today

51:41.131 --> 51:44.067
So, whatever you gotta do

51:44.068 --> 51:47.299
You got a lovely day
to do it in, that's true

51:53.811 --> 51:55.802
Good morning, Charlie.

51:58.115 --> 51:59.844
Good morning.

52:00.184 --> 52:02.051
This is Sofia, Charlie.

52:02.052 --> 52:04.420
She's a magician
with a needle.

52:04.421 --> 52:07.523
Sofia's workin' me up
a little Glen Plaid number,

52:07.524 --> 52:10.187
and I've asked her if
she'd put something
together for you.

52:10.794 --> 52:13.096
I don't need
any clothes, Colonel.

52:13.097 --> 52:16.157
Standard issue
for an upscale
urban assignment.

52:16.467 --> 52:19.135
You don't like the clothes,
Charlie,
on completion of duty,

52:19.136 --> 52:21.161
you can give 'em away.

52:21.472 --> 52:24.907
Juice, coffee,
and other assorted goodies
on the trolley over there.

52:24.908 --> 52:27.138
Get yourself up,
get yourself together.

52:28.245 --> 52:31.414
It's a great day
for singin' a song

52:31.415 --> 52:34.851
And it's a great day
for movin' along

52:34.852 --> 52:37.520
And it's a great day
from morning to night

52:37.521 --> 52:39.512
And it's a great day

52:40.958 --> 52:42.687
For everybody's plight

52:49.199 --> 52:51.167
How are you feeling
today, Colonel?

52:51.168 --> 52:52.535
Super!

52:52.536 --> 52:54.170
Superior!

52:54.171 --> 52:55.764
Superfluous!

52:57.174 --> 52:59.506
Young Sofie here
is working Thanksgiving

52:59.910 --> 53:02.178
because she's trying to
put herself through college.

53:02.179 --> 53:05.314
I told her, "My young friend
Charlie's headed for college."

53:05.315 --> 53:06.916
Excuse me.

53:06.917 --> 53:08.217
Where you goin'?

53:08.218 --> 53:09.919
I need to use
the phone.

53:09.920 --> 53:12.150
What's wrong with
the phones in here?

53:12.689 --> 53:14.390
I don't want
to disturb you.

53:14.391 --> 53:16.951
You're not disturbing me.
Make your call.

53:17.594 --> 53:18.795
I'd kind of like
to be private.

53:18.796 --> 53:20.457
Stay out of my room!

53:21.699 --> 53:23.758
This is as private
as you're gonna get.

53:26.870 --> 53:30.898
But if
you've got somethin'
that must be done

53:31.708 --> 53:35.145
And it can only
be done by one

53:36.980 --> 53:38.209
Sofia,

53:39.783 --> 53:42.275
what are the chances
of suitin' you
up sometime?

53:43.954 --> 53:46.981
Sugarbush Lodge.
George Willis, please.

53:49.793 --> 53:50.993
Hello.

53:50.994 --> 53:52.587
George! Hey, it's Charlie.

53:53.130 --> 53:56.293
Hey, Chas.
Next year you gotta
come up with us.

53:56.734 --> 53:59.669
White powder on
a base of snow bunnies.

54:01.305 --> 54:03.398
Chas, are you there?

54:04.007 --> 54:05.842
Yeah, I'm here.

54:05.843 --> 54:08.277
You told me to call
you for the moves.

54:08.278 --> 54:09.612
All right.

54:09.613 --> 54:13.015
For now, the move's
no move, status quo.

54:13.016 --> 54:14.817
Everything's
the way we left it.

54:14.818 --> 54:16.286
How did we leave it?

54:17.121 --> 54:20.113
See no evil,
hear no eviI.

54:21.358 --> 54:23.326
You know
what I mean, Chas?

54:24.695 --> 54:27.562
Yeah. See no evil,
hear no evil.

54:29.900 --> 54:32.101
Okay, then,
walk like you talk.

54:32.102 --> 54:34.332
All right, bye.

54:35.272 --> 54:37.070
George Willis, huh?

54:38.075 --> 54:39.235
Yeah.

54:39.977 --> 54:41.544
George Willis.

54:41.545 --> 54:44.810
That makes his
father probably
George Willis, Senior.

54:45.883 --> 54:47.884
Charlie, I ask you,

54:47.885 --> 54:51.888
what do you think
big George is gonna feel
about little George

54:51.889 --> 54:54.949
seeing no evil,
hearing no evil?

54:57.494 --> 54:59.622
Well, we're not gonna
tell our parents.

54:59.830 --> 55:02.731
We're just gonna keep it
between ourselves.

55:03.400 --> 55:06.267
Oh, George isn't gonna tell
his father about this thing!

55:07.037 --> 55:08.271
Damn decent of him.

55:10.007 --> 55:12.141
Scusi, Colonnello.
Prego.

55:12.142 --> 55:13.906
I love it
when you hurt me.

55:15.479 --> 55:17.346
Tell me now,
Charlie.

55:17.347 --> 55:21.307
This George Willis, Jr.,
what's his father do?

55:22.286 --> 55:23.853
I don't really know.

55:23.854 --> 55:25.686
Well, I'm gonna tell you.

55:26.056 --> 55:27.924
When George Willis, Senior,

55:27.925 --> 55:30.726
isn't busy as
a million-dollar man
for Aetna Casualty...

55:30.727 --> 55:32.962
Or is it
New England distributor

55:32.963 --> 55:34.597
for the Chrysler
Corporation?

55:34.598 --> 55:38.592
He concerns himself
with his young son,
George Willis, Jr.

55:39.570 --> 55:42.038
George isn't going
to say anything
to his father.

55:42.039 --> 55:43.802
Oh, Charlie.

55:44.241 --> 55:46.576
Big George is gonna
wind up little George,

55:46.577 --> 55:49.679
and little George
is gonna sing
like a canary.

55:49.680 --> 55:52.171
And if you're hip, kid,
you're gonna hop to, too.

55:52.583 --> 55:54.784
You've got this
all figured out,
don't you?

55:54.785 --> 55:57.086
It don't take no
Young American merit

55:57.087 --> 55:58.988
scholarship to
figure this one out.

55:58.989 --> 56:01.090
Charlie,
you had a little life,

56:01.091 --> 56:03.192
so you decided
to go to the
Baird school

56:03.193 --> 56:05.560
to put yourself
in the market
for a big one.

56:05.963 --> 56:07.930
Now, in order to stay
in the running,

56:07.931 --> 56:10.992
you're gonna have
to tell these people
what they want to know.

56:12.302 --> 56:13.636
You think so?

56:13.637 --> 56:15.104
Are we finished, Sofia?

56:15.105 --> 56:16.766
Yes.
Grazie. Grazie.
Andate.

56:19.910 --> 56:21.434
Charlie,

56:22.613 --> 56:24.843
if you don't sing now,

56:25.515 --> 56:28.951
you're gonna end up,
not only shelving biscuits

56:28.952 --> 56:31.988
in some convenience store
in the Oregon 'burbs,

56:31.989 --> 56:34.924
but probably the last
word you'll ever hear
yourself say

56:34.925 --> 56:37.226
just before you croak,
gonna be,

56:37.227 --> 56:41.097
"Have a nice day
and come back soon."

56:41.098 --> 56:42.999
Sofia!

56:43.000 --> 56:44.867
Measure up
Charlie, here, pronto.

56:44.868 --> 56:46.802
We got a date
for Thanksgiving.

56:47.471 --> 56:48.734
We got a date?

56:49.006 --> 56:50.837
My brother's place.

56:50.974 --> 56:54.137
W.R. Slade,
White Plains, New York.

56:54.811 --> 56:57.212
Colonel, I can't go with you
to your brother's place.

56:57.347 --> 57:00.340
I mean, I should be
getting back to school.

57:03.253 --> 57:07.023
Well, you gotta have
Thanksgiving somewhere.

57:07.024 --> 57:09.191
I mean, eats and treats.

57:09.192 --> 57:11.024
I can use
the company, Charlie.

57:14.531 --> 57:15.998
All right.

57:15.999 --> 57:17.566
Does he know
I'm comin'?

57:17.567 --> 57:19.035
He doesn't know
I'm comin'.

57:19.036 --> 57:21.137
But wait till you see
the look on his face

57:21.138 --> 57:22.538
when I walk
through the door.

57:22.539 --> 57:24.098
Oh, he loves me!

57:26.376 --> 57:30.346
Oh, Charlie,
about your
little problem,

57:30.347 --> 57:33.015
there are two kinds
of people in this world:

57:33.016 --> 57:35.418
Those who stand up
and face the music,

57:35.419 --> 57:37.320
and those who
run for cover.

57:37.321 --> 57:38.955
Cover's better.

57:38.956 --> 57:41.157
Okay, Sofia, suit him up!

57:41.158 --> 57:42.785
Make him pretty.

57:59.242 --> 58:00.835
Careful.

58:02.145 --> 58:03.511
Should I ring it?
Yeah.

58:12.923 --> 58:15.187
Yes?
Yes!

58:15.359 --> 58:16.758
Who is this?

58:17.127 --> 58:18.617
It's Randy.

58:18.795 --> 58:20.627
Randy? You new?

58:21.698 --> 58:23.165
I'm your nephew.

58:23.166 --> 58:25.601
Hah! Here I am!

58:25.836 --> 58:27.737
Your sister's been
hoarding me
long enough.

58:27.738 --> 58:30.707
Thought it's time
to spread the
riches around.

58:31.141 --> 58:33.476
Uncle Frank.
Gloria!

58:33.477 --> 58:35.445
Gail.
Of course.

58:36.246 --> 58:39.148
Say hello to the potluck
party from New York City.

58:39.149 --> 58:42.618
Good old Uncle
Frank and this here
with him is Charlie Simms,

